<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Ceanothus papillosus </i>is a short-lived obligate seeder that dominates stands for several years following fires. However, there is no post-fire demographic information for this shrub (Borchert et al. 2004). A fire cycle of 20-50 years should promote <i>C. papillosus</i>.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (20-100 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
